This paper deals with the problem of personalization of online services from the viewpoint of ad targeting, which involves ranking ad categories based on a user's preference. This problem can be approached from various sub-fields of computer science, such as machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given that the paper proposes a novel label ranking approach capable of efficiently learning non-linear, highly accurate models in large-scale settings, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
